Cursor-based Pagination
MyCase uses cursor-based pagination. Cursor based pagination uses a cursor(query parameter) to know what items to fetch next.

We break up results into smaller subsets and return them in pages. We default to 25 items per page but you can modify the page size using the page_size query parameter. The maximum items per page that we allow is 1,000.

$ curl -I "http://example.com/v1/cases?page_size=40"
To navigate a paginated resource collection, request the first page of items and if there are more pages a Link header (see RFC 5988 for more information ) will be added to the response. This link should be utilized to retrieve the next page and will expire after 3 days.

Example:

Link: <http://example.com/v1/cases?page_size=40&page_token=abc>; rel="next"
